xediaEthernetMIB.name: xediaEthernetMIB
xediaEthernetMIB.description: This module defines proprietary objects that extend those in IETF's the Ethernet-Like Interface MIB.

xdot3StatsTable.name: xdot3StatsTable
xdot3StatsTable.description: Additional Xedia proprietary statistics for ethernet-like interfaces.

xdot3StatsEntry.name: xdot3StatsEntry
xdot3StatsEntry.description: Additional Xedia proprietary statistics for single ethernet-like interface.

xdot3StatsOutUnderflows.name: xdot3StatsOutUnderflows
xdot3StatsOutUnderflows.description: A count of frames not transmitted on a particular interface because of underflow. An underflow occurs when the driver does not keep up with the hardware's transmit speed in providing buffers.

xdot3StatsOutNoCarriers.name: xdot3StatsOutNoCarriers
xdot3StatsOutNoCarriers.description: The number of times that the carrier signal from the transceiver was not present when a frame was to be transmitted.

xdot3StatsOutCarrierLosses.name: xdot3StatsOutCarrierLosses
xdot3StatsOutCarrierLosses.description: The number of times the carrier was lost during transmission.

xdot3StatsOutJabberTimeouts.name: xdot3StatsOutJabberTimeouts
xdot3StatsOutJabberTimeouts.description: The number of times a transmission was aborted because the jabber timer timed out.

xdot3StatsOutTotalCollisions.name: xdot3StatsOutTotalCollisions
xdot3StatsOutTotalCollisions.description: The total number of collisions that have occurred while transmitting on this interface.

xdot3StatsInDescriptorErrors.name: xdot3StatsInDescriptorErrors
xdot3StatsInDescriptorErrors.description: The number of frames that were truncated because they did not fit within the current desriptor buffers.

xdot3StatsInRunts.name: xdot3StatsInRunts
xdot3StatsInRunts.description: The number of runt frames. A runt frame may have been damaged by collision or premature termination before the collision window had passed.

xdot3StatsInTotalCollisions.name: xdot3StatsInTotalCollisions
xdot3StatsInTotalCollisions.description: The number of collisions detected on incoming frames.

xdot3StatsInDribbles.name: xdot3StatsInDribbles
xdot3StatsInDribbles.description: The number of frames which were not a multiple of 8 bytes.

xdot3StatsInOverflows.name: xdot3StatsInOverflows
xdot3StatsInOverflows.description: The number of frames that were truncated due to FIFO overflow. This indicates a hardware problem (as opposed to MissedFrames which indicates the software did not keep up).

xdot3StatsInMissedFrames.name: xdot3StatsInMissedFrames
xdot3StatsInMissedFrames.description: The number of frames that were received by the hardware but that were not picked up by the driver.

xdot3NegotiatedConfigSpeed.name: xdot3NegotiatedConfigSpeed
xdot3NegotiatedConfigSpeed.description: The negotiated configured speed of the interface when the auto negotiates mode is enable.

xdot3NegotiatedConfigDuplexMode.name: xdot3NegotiatedConfigDuplexMode
xdot3NegotiatedConfigDuplexMode.description: The negotiated configured duplex mode of the interface.

xdot3NegotiatedFlowControl.name: xdot3NegotiatedFlowControl
xdot3NegotiatedFlowControl.description: The negotiated configured flow control parameters.

xdot3IfOperStatus.name: xdot3IfOperStatus
xdot3IfOperStatus.description: This is a reference object (from the ifmib.mi2's ifOperStatus) reports the current operational states of the interface for the auto-negotiate configuration purpose.

xdot3ConfigTable.name: xdot3ConfigTable
xdot3ConfigTable.description: Xedia proprietary configuration parameters for ethernet-like interfaces.

xdot3ConfigEntry.name: xdot3ConfigEntry
xdot3ConfigEntry.description: Xedia proprietary configuration parameters for single ethernet-like interface.

xdot3ConfigSpeed.name: xdot3ConfigSpeed
xdot3ConfigSpeed.description: The configured speed of the interface. This may be set by the administrator or may be the result of auto-negotiation.

xdot3ConfigDuplexMode.name: xdot3ConfigDuplexMode
xdot3ConfigDuplexMode.description: The configured mode of the interface.

xdot3ConfigMedia.name: xdot3ConfigMedia
xdot3ConfigMedia.description: The media type of the interface. The value 'tx(1)' indicates copper, 'fx(2)' indicates 850 nm multi-mode fiber, 'sx(3)' indicates 850 nm multi-mode fiber and lx(4) indicates 1300 nm single-mode or multi-mode fiber.

xdot3ConfigCaptureEffectResol.name: xdot3ConfigCaptureEffectResol
xdot3ConfigCaptureEffectResol.description: This object controls whether a non-standard backoff algorithm is used for collision handling in order to avoid 'capture effect'. Capture effect occurs when two stations transmit in such a way that, because of collision backoff, one station captures the channel for an unfair amount of time (and the line may remain idle for a long time after that station stops transmitting because of the second station increasing its backoff time.) The value of 'enabled(1)' indicates the enhanced algorithm will be use. The value 'disabled(2)' is the default and indicates the standard backoff algorithm is used.

xdot3ConfigAutoNegotiate.name: xdot3ConfigAutoNegotiate
xdot3ConfigAutoNegotiate.description: This object controls whether to negotiate the speed and duplex mode for 10/100 fast ethernet; and negotiate duplex mode and MAC control for gigabit ethernet interface.

xdot3Compliance.name: xdot3Compliance
xdot3Compliance.description: The compliance statement for all agents that support this MIB. A compliant agent implements all objects defined in this MIB.

xdot3Group.name: xdot3Group
xdot3Group.description: The set of all accessible objects in this MIB.
